# Comprehensive EDA Summary: Nepal Used Car Market Dataset (847 Vehicles)

## 1. Dataset Overview
- **Size**: 847 cleaned listings
- **Price Range**: NPR 1,50,000 → NPR 2,40,00,000
- **Average Price**: NPR 23,42,220 (~23.4 Lakh)
- **Median Price**: NPR 17,70,000
- **Year Range**: 1975–2023 (average 2013.3, median 2014)
- **Average Engine**: 1,524 CC
- **Average Odometer**: 51,112 km
- **Average Mileage**: 18.91 km/l
- **No missing values** — fully cleaned dataset

## 2. Key Numerical Relationships (Correlations)
- Price ↔ Engine CC: **+0.394 (moderate positive — bigger engines = higher price)
- Price ↔ Odometer: -0.166 (weak negative — higher mileage slightly lowers price)
- Engine CC ↔ Odometer: +0.104 (almost no relationship)

## 3. Price Segmentation by Engine Size (Very Clear Pattern)

| Engine Category      | Count | Avg Price (NPR) | Avg Odometer | Price Premium |
|----------------------|-------|------------------|--------------|----------------|
| Small (≤1200 CC)     | 406   | 17,30,136       | 47,823 km    | Baseline      |
| Medium (1201–2000 CC)| 300   | 24,49,238       | 52,154 km    | +41% vs small |
| Large (>2000 CC)     | 141   | 38,76,979       | 58,364 km    | +124% vs small |

→ Clear and strong trend: every additional ~800–1000 CC adds roughly NPR 8-12 Lakh in market value.

## 4. Depreciation vs Mileage (Surprisingly Moderate)

| Mileage Group         | Count | Avg Price (NPR) | Price Drop    | % Drop |
|-----------------------|-------|------------------|---------------|--------|
| Low (≤50k km)         | 447   | 27,34,750       | –             | –      |
| Medium (50–150k km)   | 393   | 19,11,202       | –8,23,548     | –30.1% |
| High (>150k km)       | 7     | 14,75,000       | –4,36,202     | –22.8% |

→ Depreciation is real but not dramatic. Cars lose ~30% from low to medium mileage, then only another ~23% even at very high mileage. Nepali buyers appear relatively tolerant of higher odometer readings.

